<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOWN GETS $106,000 FOR NONEXISTENT POLICE DEPT.  
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This town of 340 people has received a $106,000 federal grant to fight 
crime.Now all it needs is a police department. 
</P>
<P>
 Town officials said they were surprised to learn they were among the first 392 
municipalities to share $200 million designated by the federal crime bill for 
hiring police officers. 
</P>
<P>
 "All we need is a part-time officer, three nights a week on weekends," said 
David Lindsey, one of the town's two councilors. "We don't have no trouble the 
rest of the time. A retired policeman who will work cheap is all we need." The 
town laid off its only officer in April because there was no money to pay him. 
</P>
