<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLITICAL SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 24 days to go before Californians go to the polls. 
</P>
<P>
 THE GOVERNOR'S RACE 
</P>
<P>
 * What Happened Friday: Republican Pete Wilson and Democrat Kathleen Brown 
debated for one hour in Sacramento and the event was broadcast statewide.Each 
then attended a post-debate party of supporters. Wilson also met with state 
correctional officers at the town of Galt, near Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 * What's Ahead: Wilson is scheduled to participate in a get-out-the vote rally 
in Sacramento. Brown planned to attend rallies in the Oakland and Los Angeles 
areas. 
</P>
<P>
 NOTABLE QUOTE 
</P>
<P>
 "Kathleen Brown's economic plan is in fact a new tax plan." 
</P>
<P>
 -- New Pete Wilson television campaign ad 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a lie. . . . The only new tax in Kathleen Brown's plan is an excise 
tax on ammunition, the proceeds of which will fund the buyback of assault 
weapons." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Brown campaign's rebuttal of new Wilson ad 
</P>
