<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: COMPTON; PROTEST ASKS 
FASTER PROBE OF OFFICER ACCUSED OF ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Latino activists urged Los Angeles County Dist. Atty. Gil Garcetti on Friday 
to quicken his investigation of a Compton police officer accused of assaulting 
a teen-ager in July. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're here . . . to ask our district attorney to give us some kind of 
finding," said Art Pulito of the Community Coalition for Justice. "It's been 
almost three months and nothing has happened."  
</P>
<P>
 Mike Botula, a spokesman for the district attorney's office, said Garcetti 
isn't stalling.  
</P>
<P>
 "These investigations do take time," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The protest outside the Downtown Criminal Courts Building came as a result of 
the July 29 incident in which 17-year-old Felipe Soltero was shown on a 
neighbor's videotape being struck by Compton Police Officer Michael Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
 The officer was called to the scene that day to assist a social worker who was 
visiting the house, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
