<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; MARCH 
PLANNED TO PROTEST IMMIGRATION INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tens of thousands of demonstrators are expected to march Sunday from the 
Eastside to Downtown in protest of Proposition 187, the state initiative that 
would bar education, social services and non-emergency health care to illegal 
immigrants. 
</P>
<P>
 City workers will close off the intersection of 1st and Spring streets at 4 
a.m. Sunday to construct a stage. 
</P>
<P>
 These streets will be closed from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.: Main Street between Aliso 
and 2nd streets; Spring Street between Cesar Chavez Avenue and 2nd Street; 1st 
and Temple streets between Broadway and Los Angeles Street; Lorena Street 
between 1st and Indiana streets, and Cesar Chavez between Indiana and Spring 
streets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
