</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am sick about the baseball strike. The hockey strike, too, is very 
distressing. 
</P>
<P>
 But what upsets me most is the failure of the NBA players to initiate a work 
action.After all, as an 11-year Clipper season ticket-holder, I am less than 
enthusiastic about the start of the season and I was hoping I wouldn't have to 
go. 
</P>
<P>
 With a 300-plus-pound Stanley Roberts, the Clippers' typical inability to sign 
their draft picks, the departure of several key starters and their failure to 
complete any significant trades, this team will be lucky to win 15 games. 
</P>
<P>
 With an organization like this, a strike looks like the only way to avoid 
another disappointing season. 
</P>
<P>
