<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COSTA MESA; WALKATHON FOR CHOC TO DRAW 6,000 PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 6,000 people are expected to participate in a walkathon Sunday to 
benefit Children's Hospital of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is at 6:30 a.m. next to the Performing Arts Center near South 
Coast Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 The walk begins at 8:30 a.m. and is sponsored by CHOC. It costs $25 to enter, 
and participants who raise $1,000 through sponsors can win a weeklong trip to 
Walt Disney World in Florida. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to have babies in strollers, kids in wagons, and people walking 
in costumes just for fun," said Janet Nagurski, a support group assistant for 
the hospital's fund-raising activities. "The money goes to help for the 
children's care. This way, no child will be turned away. It's kind of like 
socialized medicine." 
</P>
<P>
 Children's Hospital, in the city of Orange, is the only pediatric facility in 
Orange County. This is the fourth consecutive year the hospital has held the 
five-kilometer walk, which takes in South Coast Plaza and surrounding area. 
</P>
<P>
 Walkers can win prizes, depending on how much money they raise from their 
sponsors. TOM RAGAN 
</P>
