</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Traffic delays may occur when work on Encino's drainage system begins in 
December, but the improvements should be worth the inconvenience, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "When completed, this project should substantially ease chronic flooding in 
the surrounding area," Los Angeles County Supervisor Ed Edelman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Workers plan to install about 7,000 feet of storm drain pipe beneath Haskell 
Avenue, Ventura Boulevard and Hartsook Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The $1.53-million contract will be carried out by workers of Malden Buntich 
Construction of Sunland and administered by the county's Department of Public 
Works. 
</P>
<P>
 While the work may close some lanes to through traffic, local access will 
remain open at all times, Edelman said. 
</P>
