<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks residents getting a head start on spring cleaning can dump trash 
for free at the Simi Valley Landfill Sunday from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The landfill will not accept tires, asbestos or any kind of hazardous 
waste.But residents can bring any other sort of household junk to 2801 Madera 
Road in Simi Valley. Proof of residency in Thousand Oaks is required. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday's event marks the first time Thousand Oaks has held a free disposal day 
at the Simi Valley Landfill. The city will continue to sponsor its Community 
Cleanu-Up Day in Thousand Oaks on Memorial Day weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Simi Valley Landfill at 522-7023. STEPHANIE 
