<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; UNION ENDORSES 2 INCUMBENTS, HORNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ojai teachers union announced Thursday that it is backing trustees Muriel 
Lavender and Vince France along with candidate Rikki Horne in the race for 
three school board seats. 
</P>
<P>
 Representing 165 teachers and counselors in the Ojai Unified School District, 
the Ojai Federation of Teachers made its endorsements after hearing the six 
candidates in the race speak at a recent forum, union President Don Ainsworth 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lavender and France won endorsements, Ainsworth said, because of their policy 
of involving teachers in district decisions. 
</P>
<P>
 Four challengers are vying for the seats held by Lavender, France and Robert 
Emhardt, who is not seeking reelection. Of the four, the union endorsed Horne, 
Ainsworth said. 
</P>
<P>
 Horne, who owns a medical claims management business, is "very highly 
educated," Ainsworth said. Also, he said, union officials were impressed by 
Horne's distaste for censorship in the schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The district was rocked by controversy last year when some parents said a 
literature anthology used in the schools contained passages that were 
inappropriate for children. 
</P>
<P>
 Horne, Ainsworth said, "felt that all citizens ought to be involved in the 
adoption process of a textbook and we shouldn't be barring students from 
reading a textbook." 
</P>
<P>
 Although the union sometimes refrains from making endorsements in school board 
races, Ainsworth said it decided to take a stand in this election. 
</P>
<P>
 "This race seems to be more closely contested than it has in the past, so we 
felt we needed to listen to all the candidates and make a choice," he said. 
MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
