<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN FACES MORE CHARGES OF MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NANCY HSU, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A San Juan Capistrano man already facing charges that he molested 10 girls in 
South County has been charged with additional counts of molestation. 
</P>
<P>
 At his preliminary hearing Friday in Laguna Niguel Municipal Court for the 
South County charges, Thomas Michael Cimino, 30, was charged with two more 
counts involving one of the girls. 
</P>
<P>
 Charges also were filed in Los Angeles last week involving a Culver City girl. 
</P>
<P>
 Cimino, who is free on $100,000 bail, will surrender to authorities next week 
on the Los Angeles charges, his attorney said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The preliminary hearing here will resume Oct 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County sheriff's deputies arrested Cimino June 20 after they showed 
pictures of him to 10 girls age 6 to 10 in Dana Point, San Clemente and San 
Juan Capistrano, Sheriff's Investigator Mark Simon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities allege that Cimino lured girls from their homes and in parks by 
asking if they could help him find his black-and-white cat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101594-0185 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 088851 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 15, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
