<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; THERAPISTS' GROUP OFFERS WORKSHOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ready to kill your spouse? Is your inner critic driving you crazy? Or perhaps 
you'd simply like to know more about sex in the '90s? 
</P>
<P>
 If so, the San Fernando Valley chapter of the California Assn. of Marriage and 
Family Therapists may have the answer for you. 
</P>
<P>
 The chapter will present a series of workshops today at Valley College that 
will focus on reducing stress, improving relationships and enhancing 
self-esteem. 
</P>
<P>
 "Surviving and Thriving in the '90s" will feature 36 workshops divided into 
six one-hour sessions that allow participants to concentrate on improving one 
aspect of their lives or focus on a variety of personal growth concerns. 
</P>
<P>
 Courses range from "How to Stay Married Without Killing Each Other" to 
"Secrets of Self-Esteem" and "Dealing With Life's Shocks and Aftershocks." 
</P>
<P>
 Workshops will be held from 8:15 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. at Valley College's Monarch 
Hall-Campus Center. Registration fee is $43 at the door. For information, call 
(818) 988-3911. ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</TEXT>
