<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN IN TRUCK KILLS DAUGHTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 34-year-old Sylmar man accidentally ran over and killed his 4-year-old 
daughter Friday when the girl ran into the path of his pickup truck, the 
California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Francisco Olea Barragan had backed up about 20 feet with a load of lumber in 
his truck when his daughter, Lydia O. Garcia, ran into its path, CHP Officer 
Rich Perez said. The accident occurred at a ranch near Sierra Highway and 
Foothill Boulevard just before 1 p.m., Perez said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He didn't realize she was standing behind the truck and he ran over the 
daughter," Perez said. 
</P>
<P>
 No further details were available Friday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
