PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; MONTANA MAY SIT OUT MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joe Montana isn't certain that he will be able to play in Denver on Monday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think the ribs are the main concern," Montana said Friday after missing 
practice all week because of two sacks and seven knockdowns he took in Kansas 
City's 20-6 loss at San Diego last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Bronco quarterback John Elway said he is recovered from his jammed and bruised 
right thumb. 
