<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; REFRIGERATOR IS DEFEATED BY BROTHERLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brotherly, ridden by Eddie Garcia, defeated Refrigerator by a half-length to 
win the $100,000 Los Alamitos Championship Invitational on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Charles-Treece trained Brotherly raced 440 yards in 21.57 seconds and paid 
$10.20 as the second choice in the wagering. 
</P>
<P>
 The gelding, owned by the partnership of Barham, Shannon and Loeb, also earned 
a berth in the Champion of Champions, in which he might again face 
Refrigerator, on Dec. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 By finishing second, Refrigerator became quarter horse racing's first 
$2-million winner with earnings of $2,006,867. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-year-old world champion, who won the past two runnings of the Los 
Alamitos Championship, bumped with Avison at the start of Friday night's race. 
</P>
<P>
 Seals finished third and Avison was fourth. Sound Dash finished fifth, 
followed by Sigs First Call. STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101594-0237 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 088903 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
