<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; LATE FIELD GOAL LEAVES BUENA WITH TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA GRALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marco Garcia of Dos Pueblos High booted a 24-yard field goal with five seconds 
remaining to force Buena to settle for a 27-27 tie in a Channel League game 
Friday night at Ventura High. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena (5-1-1, 2-0-1 in league play) led the entire game until Garcia's kick 
and had taken a 27-17 lead when Jeff Stetler scored on a 14-yard pass from 
Glenn Dudley late in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But Dos Pueblos (2-3-1, 1-1-1) pulled within three when Ryan Thompson returned 
the ensuing kickoff 96 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena's Chris Carr led all rushers with 133 yards in 18 carries. Josh Cross 
added 52 yards in 11 carries and scored on a 17-yard run in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Stewart had two of Buena's touchdowns, scoring on a three-yard option 
pass from Carr in the second quarter to give the Bulldogs a 14-3 halftime lead, 
and again on a one-yard run in the third period as the Bulldogs took a 20-9 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Dudley completed eight of 13 for 83 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Ertman caught four passes for 44 yards and Stetler added two catches for 
26 yards for the Bulldogs. LISA GRALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
