<P>
GIOVANNETTONE LEADS CHAMINADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TERRY BROWN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Jason Giovannettone rushed for 112 yards in 21 carries and scored 
four touchdowns to lead Chaminade High to a 34-12 victory over St. Bernard in a 
Mission League opener Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Giovannettone also caught four passes for 27 yards and Tyler Fenwick had four 
receptions for 82 yards. The Eagles (4-2, 1-0) struck early as quarterback Tom 
Racius connected on a 58-yard touchdown pass to Fenwick on the second play of 
the game. Racius completed 13 of 28 for 148 yards and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade forced five fumbles, had five sacks and one interception while 
holding the Vikings (3-3, 0-1) to 88 yards. TERRY BROWN 
