<P>
FRANKLIN OUTSHOOTS VERDUGO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOSEPH WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Franklin High used a run-and-shoot offense to outgun Verdugo Hills, 41-7, in a 
Northern Conference game Friday afternoon at Franklin. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills took a 7-0 lead when junior tailback Ishmael Dukes scored on a 
77-yard touchdown run on the game's first play from scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Franklin quarterback Jeff Deno shredded the Dons, completing 16 of 21 
passes for 244 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnie Sanders caught four passes for 121 yards, including touchdowns of 41 
yards, one yard and 74 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Dukes gained 96 yards in five carries. JOSEPH WRIGHT 
</P>
