<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SOUTH COAST LEAGUE; MACKENZIE LEADS 
CAPISTRANO VALLEY OVER SAN CLEMENTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore running back Malaefou MacKenzie scored three touchdowns to lead 
Capistrano Valley to a 21-9 South Coast League victory over San Clemente Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 MacKenzie carried 29 times for 92 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars' second possession of the game was all MacKenzie. He carried the 
ball on every down, nine times for 42 yards, finishing it with a three-yard 
touchdown run with 3 minutes 4 seconds left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 MacKenzie put Capistrano Valley (4-2, 1-0) up 14-0, on a 12-yard run with 4:16 
left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougar defense stuffed San Clemente (3-3, 0-1) in the first half, holding 
the Tritons to 51 yards total offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Triton quarterback Jeff Carlin was pressured all night by Cougar defenders 
Andrew Klein and Jason Purvis, who sacked him four times. Purvis was in on 
three of those. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlin, who scored the Tritons' only touchdown on a one-yard run in the third 
quarter, had averaged more than 200 yards per game passing before the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Friday night the Cougar's secondary, led by defensive back, Jeffrey Brion and 
linebacker Sam Petke held Carlin to 115 yards, completing 13 of 31 passes. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente had an opportunity to get the ball back, down 14-9, with less 
than three minutes remaining, but a roughing-the-kicker call gave Capistrano 
Valley a first down and MacKenzie wrapped up the victory with a nine-yard 
touchdown run with 45 seconds left. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
