<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BRETHREN CHRISTIAN CONTINUES TO SKID 
WITH 33-0 LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Last season, Brethren Christian went to the Division X title game. This 
season, it might be more at home in Steve Harvey's Bottom Ten. 
</P>
<P>
 Brethren Christian lost its fifth straight game Friday night, 33-0, to Valley 
Christian (5-1, 1-0) in the Olympic League opener at Valley Christian High. 
</P>
<P>
 It didn't take the Crusaders long to capitalize on a 15-yard punt by Warrior 
Tim Novinger. 
</P>
<P>
 Jonathan DeBie caught a seven-yard touchdown pass from Kirk Saarloos with 5 
minutes 4 seconds remaining in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Brethren Christian (1-5, 0-1) tried a fake punt on its next possession, but 
Horacio Freijo was stopped short of a first down. 
</P>
<P>
 Three plays later, Jason VanDuyn ran 43 yards for a score. He rushed for 165 
yards in 26 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Cunningham gave the Crusaders a 21-0 lead on a two-yard run with 6:34 
left in the third quarter. Heidi VanderFeer kicked the conversion for her first 
extra point of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Lee intercepted a pass by Brethren Christian quarterback Ryan Babcock and 
returned it 11 yards for a score. 
</P>
<P>
 Cunningham finished the scoring, going 48 yards with 1:08 left in the game. He 
rushed for 92 yards in 11 carries. RUSSELL BANKS 
