<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ryan Johansen directed second-half touchdown drives of 77 and 74 yards to lead 
Pacifica past Santiago, 15-3, in a Garden Grove League game at Garden Grove 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago's Jose Palacios booted a 32-yard field goal in the second quarter to 
give the Cavaliers (2-4, 1-1) the lead at halftime, but the Mariners wasted 
little time in pulling ahead in the second half. 
</P>
