<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; CORONA DEL MAR RALLIES WITH BIG PLAYS 
TO BEAT EL TORO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SPINN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Big plays and huge gains were common at Newport Harbor Friday night, but there 
wasn't anything ordinary about the finish of Corona del Mar's 35-28 Sea View 
League victory over El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Hogan led the Sea Kings, rushing for 271 yards in 23 carries, including 
touchdown runs of 96 (a school record) and 74 yards, as Corona del Mar rallied 
from a 21-7 first-half deficit. 
</P>
<P>
 Hogan's 74-yard scoring run with 2 minutes, 17 seconds left in the game 
touched off a frantic set of events. Corona del Mar (3-3, 1-0) trailed, 28-21, 
before Hogan went off tackle and then cut up the left sideline for the long 
touchdown that made the score 28-27.  
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar then went for two, with quarterback Josh Walz scrambling into 
the end zone for the conversion to give the Sea Kings a 29-28 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 After the kickoff, El Toro (3-3, 0-1) quickly moved into Corona del Mar 
territory, but faced a fourth-and-eight situation at the Sea King 44-yard line. 
Corona del Mar defensive back Aaron Perlmutter then appeared to clinch the 
victory by intercepting El Toro's Brian Wilson and returning 73 yards for a 
touchdown and a 35-28 Sea King lead with 35 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Nothing was certain in this game, however, as El Toro's Joe Ader returned the 
kickoff 50 yards to the Corona del Mar 42. Wilson tried to get off a pass as 
time was running out, but a sack by Fred Garcia finished things off. 
</P>
<P>
 Hogan's 96-yard run late in the second quarter broke the previous Sea King 
record of 94 yards set by Brian Lucas in 1989 against La Quinta. MARK SPINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
