<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO. 1 PLAYER LOSES IN WHEELCHAIR TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Welch upset top-seeded Laurent Giammartini of France on Friday in the 
quarterfinals in the men's Open Division of the U.S. Open of Wheelchair Tennis 
at the Racquet Club of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Welch, from Bedford, Tex., defeated Giammartini, 6-4, 6-2.In other matches, 
10th-seeded Jim Black of Oceanside upset second-seeded Randy Snow of of Heath, 
Tex., 4-6, 7-5, 6-4, and third-seeded David Hall of Jacksonville, Fla., 
defeated seventh-seeded Michael Foulkswon of La Jolla, 6-1, 6-2. Fourth-seeded 
Mick Connell of Australia beat eighth-seeded Scott Douglas of Pelham, Ala., 
7-6, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's Open Division, top-seeded Chantal Vandierendonck of the Netherlands 
beat fourth-seeded Daniela DiToro of Australia, 7-6, 6-4. The Netherlands' 
Monique Kalkman, seeded No. 2, beat third-seeded Regina Isecke of Germany, 6-2, 
6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 The Open Division men's semifinals and women's final are today. 
</P>
